y disease diagnosis</span></strong></a>.\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    <p\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n        <span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>5.2 Research and\r\n                Development</strong></span>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n        <span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Science continues to evolve:</span>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <ul style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-top:0cm;list-style-type:disc; list-style-position: outside;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n        <li\r\n            style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n            <strong>Focus Areas</strong>: Better biomarkers and less invasive methods.\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li\r\n            style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n            <strong>Emerging Biomarkers</strong>: Offering more precise insights into <strong>kidney health</strong>.\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li\r\n            style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n            <strong>Future Possibilities</strong>: A shift toward simpler, faster, and more patient-friendly\r\n            testing.&nbsp;\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    <p\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n        <span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>5.3 The Role of Education and\r\n                Awareness</strong></span>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n        <span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Knowledge is power in <strong>kidney\r\n                health</strong>:</span>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <ul style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-top:0cm;list-style-type:disc; list-style-position: outside;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n        <li\r\n            style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n            <strong>Public Health Campaigns</strong>: Encouraging people to get tested and reduce risks.\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li\r\n            style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n            <strong>Patient Education</strong>: Empowering patients with information about the <a\r\n                href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/blogs/10/choosing-best-nephrologist-in-india-to-keep-well-kidney-functions\"><strong><span\r\n                        style=\"color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\">kidney test</span></strong></a>.\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li\r\n            style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n            <strong>Community Support</strong>: Access to resources and support networks.<span\r\n                style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"></span>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    <p\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n        <span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><br></span>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n        <span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px;\"><strong>Overall Summary</strong></span>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n        <span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Understanding <strong>kidney function\r\n                tests</strong> is crucial for preserving <strong>kidney health</strong> and overall well-being. With\r\n            insights into how your kidneys work, available tests, and interpretation of results, you can take charge of\r\n            your health. Whether you&apos;re managing <a\r\n                href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/blogs/15/chronic-kidney-disease\"><strong><span\r\n                        style=\"color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\">chronic kidney disease (CKD)</span></strong></a> or simply\r\n            monitoring wellness, routine <strong>kidney blood tests</strong> and <strong>kidney urine tests</strong>\r\n            offer essential guidance. Always partner with your healthcare provider for accurate <strong>kidney disease\r\n                diagnosis</strong> and personalized care.</span>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n        <span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">For expert guidance and compassionate care,\r\n            consult <a href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/\"><strong><span\r\n                        style=\"color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\">Dr. Sunil Prakash</span></strong></a>, a leading nephrologist\r\n            dedicated to helping patients maintain optimal kidney health.</span>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n        <span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">&nbsp;</span>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n        <span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Frequently Asked Questions\r\n                (FAQs)</strong></span>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <ol style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-top:0cm;list-style-type:decimal; list-style-position: outside;\" start=\"1\"\r\n        type=\"1\">\r\n        <li\r\n            style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n            <strong>What are the most common kidney function tests?</strong>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n    <p\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n        <span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">&nbsp;The most common tests include serum\r\n            creatinine, BUN, eGFR, and <strong>urinalysis</strong>.</span>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <div\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'>\r\n        <ol start=\"2\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;list-style-type: decimal;\">\r\n            <li\r\n                style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'>\r\n                <strong>How often should I get my kidney function tested?</strong>\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ol>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n        <span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">It largely depends on your risk factors and\r\n            existing health conditions, but generally, annual testing is recommended for those at higher risk.</span>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <ol style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-top:0cm;list-style-type:decimal; list-style-position: outside;\" start=\"3\"\r\n        type=\"1\">\r\n        <li\r\n            style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n            <strong>What do abnormal kidney function test results mean?</strong>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n    <p\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n        <span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">They may indicate damage or dysfunction\r\n            requiring further <a\r\n                href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/blogs/15/chronic-kidney-disease\"><strong><span\r\n                        style=\"color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\">kidney disease diagnosis</span></strong></a>.</span>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <div\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'>\r\n        <ol start=\"4\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;list-style-type: decimal;\">\r\n            <li\r\n                style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'>\r\n                <strong>Can lifestyle changes improve kidney function?</strong>\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ol>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n        <span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Yes, a healthy diet, hydration, and managing\r\n            <strong>chronic conditions</strong> help.</span>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <div\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'>\r\n        <ol start=\"5\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;list-style-type: decimal;\">\r\n            <li\r\n                style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'>\r\n                <strong>Are kidney function tests painful or invasive?</strong>\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ol>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p\r\n        style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;text-align:justify;\'>\r\n        <span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Most&nbsp;</span><span\r\n            style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><a\r\n                href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/blogs/10/choosing-best-nephrologist-in-india-to-keep-well-kidney-functions\"><strong><span\r\n                        style=\"color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\">kidney blood tests</span></strong></a></span><span\r\n            style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">&nbsp;and <strong>urine tests</strong> are simple\r\n            and non-invasive.</span>\r\n    </p>', '', '', '', '2025-01-02', '', 'kidney-function-tests');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `name`, `short_desc`, `image`, `description`, `meta_title`, `meta_disc`, `meta_keyword`, `date`, `tags`, `url`) VALUES
(18, 'Polycystic Kidney Disease (PKD): Symptoms, Risks, and Treatment Options', 'A genetic condition known as polycystic kidney disease (PKD) gradually alters kidney structure and function and, if left unchecked, can result in chronic complications.', 'blog18.jpg', '<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">A genetic condition known as polycystic kidney disease (PKD) gradually alters kidney structure and function and, if left unchecked, can result in chronic complications. Even though many people are unaware of it, PKD affects more than just the kidneys.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">According to&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\"><a href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/\"><strong>Dr. Sunil Prakash</strong></a></span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>&nbsp;(Vice Chairman and Head of Department Nephrology and Renal Sciences &amp; Kidney Transplant)</strong>, for those who are at risk or have been diagnosed with this condition, prompt identification and organized care can greatly improve outcomes.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The development of multiple fluid-filled kidney cysts is a hallmark of PKD. These cysts can eventually cause the kidneys to enlarge, push out healthy tissue, and become less functional. There are two main forms: Autosomal Recessive PKD (ARPKD), which is less common in children, and Autosomal Dominant PKD (ADPKD), which is the most prevalent form that manifests in adulthood. Although it is inherited, even family members may have different levels of severity, onset age, and symptom pattern.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><br></span></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Symptoms of PKD</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\"><a href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/contact\"><strong>Polycystic Kidney Disease</strong></a></span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp;frequently goes unnoticed in the beginning. Symptoms begin to show up as the cysts enlarge and obstruct normal kidney function. Depending on how the disease develops, these symptoms may be mild at first but tend to get worse over time.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">You may experience:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc; list-style-position: inside;\">\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Persistent high blood pressure (often the earliest indicator)</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Pain in the back, sides, or abdomen</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">An enlarged abdomen due to growing kidneys</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Blood in urine (hematuria), which may come and go</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Recurrent urinary tract infections</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kidney stones</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">A general feeling of fatigue or weakness</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Many people confuse these symptoms for other, less serious conditions. This emphasizes how crucial it is to take family history into account and get medical help if kidney-related discomfort persists.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><br></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Risks and Complications</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">PKD is by no means a localized disease, even though it mainly affects the kidneys. It brings with it a range of health issues that can affect different systems and organs.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">Kidney-Specific Complications:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">End-stage kidney disease, in which the kidneys are no longer able to function properly, is one of the most dangerous outcomes. Dialysis or a kidney transplant are now required. Growing cysts can also result in persistent pain, particularly in the abdomen and lower back. Urinary tract and kidney cyst infections can become painful, common, and challenging to treat.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">Complications Beyond the Kidneys:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Many patients also face issues outside the renal system. These may include:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;\">\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Liver cysts</strong>, especially in women, which can lead to discomfort or fullness in the abdomen.</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Cerebral aneurysms</strong>, particularly in patients with a family history of stroke, which may rupture if undiagnosed.</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Heart valve issues</strong>, such as mitral valve prolapse, which could require monitoring or intervention.</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Digestive complications</strong>, like diverticulosis, which involves small pouches in the colon wall that may become infected or inflamed.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Patients with PKD benefit from a coordinated care plan that involves multiple specialists because these complications can manifest in multiple organs.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><br></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Diagnosis and Monitoring</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\"><a href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/contact\"><strong>Polycystic Kidney Disease</strong></a></span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp;is frequently found when conducting routine health screenings or when looking into symptoms like abdominal pain or hypertension. The first step is typically a renal ultrasound, a straightforward, non-invasive test that can detect cysts.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Doctors might use MRIs or CT scans for a more thorough assessment, particularly if the results of an ultrasound are unclear. Genetic testing can verify the existence of PKD-linked mutations in situations where there is a family history but no visible cysts as of yet.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Once diagnosed, ongoing monitoring is crucial. This typically includes:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;\">\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Periodic blood and urine tests to track kidney function</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Blood pressure checks, as hypertension can accelerate disease progression</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Occasional imaging studies to monitor cyst growth and organ size</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Before irreparable harm is done, proactive management is made possible by early detection, particularly in those with a family history.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><br></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Management and Treatment</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Though there is no cure for&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\"><a href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/contact\"><strong>Polycystic Kidney Disease</strong></a></span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">, several approaches to treatment can slow its progression and lessen side effects. The objective is to effectively manage related symptoms and maintain kidney function for as long as possible.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">Medical Interventions:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;\">\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The mainstay of PKD treatment is blood pressure control. Commonly used medications to lessen kidney stress include ACE inhibitors and ARBs.</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Analgesics may be beneficial for people who experience chronic pain. However, NSAID use needs to be closely watched because excessive use can damage the kidneys.</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Antibiotics are used to treat UTIs and infected cysts. Hospitalization or even surgical drainage may be necessary for certain infections.</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In some patients with rapidly worsening PKD, tolvaptan, a more recent drug, can decrease kidney volume and slow the growth of cysts. Because of the possible adverse effects, liver function needs to be regularly monitored.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">Lifestyle Modifications:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Lifestyle plays a big role in slowing the disease. Patients are encouraged to:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;\">\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Adopt a low-sodium, moderate-protein diet</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Stay hydrated with adequate water intake</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Avoid smoking and limit alcohol and caffeine</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Exercise regularly to maintain cardiovascular health</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Avoid over-the-counter medications that strain the kidneys</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Dialysis is required if kidney failure occurs. But for those who are younger or in better health, a kidney transplant is frequently the best long-term choice.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><br></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Emotional Impact and Genetic Counselling</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">A long-term diagnosis such as PKD can have a significant impact on mental and emotional health in addition to physical health. A lot of patients worry about their future, the course of their illness, and their potential offspring.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Peer support groups and professional counselling are two examples of support networks that can offer a much-needed outlet for these worries. Building emotional resilience and lowering feelings of loneliness are two benefits of having a safe place to talk about experiences.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Genetic counselling is especially helpful because PKD is a genetic disease. It assists people and families in comprehending inheritance patterns, assessing the risks to future generations, and investigating options such as preimplantation genetic diagnosis (PGD) during in vitro fertilization (IVF) for those who wish to become parents.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><br></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Overall Summary</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\"><a href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/contact\"><strong>Polycystic Kidney Disease</strong></a></span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp;is a chronic illness that affects many systems and goes unnoticed until symptoms appear. It goes beyond the kidneys. However, proactive management, early detection, and awareness do make a significant impact. Patients today can anticipate a better quality of life and more treatment options than ever before thanks to advancements in medication, improved diagnostic tools, and a more comprehensive understanding of the condition. As&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\"><a href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/\"><strong>Dr. Sunil Prakash</strong></a></span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>&nbsp;(Vice Chairman and Head of Department Nephrology and Renal Sciences &amp; Kidney Transplant)</strong> highlights, the combination of medical treatment, healthy lifestyle choices, emotional support, and routine check-ups is essential to living well with PKD. Patients can effectively manage their condition and lead active, fulfilling lives with the correct approach.</span></p>', 'Polycystic Kidney Disease (PKD): Symptoms, Risks, and Treatments', 'Learn about Polycystic Kidney Disease (PKD)its symptoms, risks, and effective treatment options. Expert insights from Dr. Sunil Prakash.', '[polycystic-kidney-disease,\r\npkd-symptoms,\r\npkd-treatment-options,\r\ndr-sunil-prakash-nephrologist,\r\nhereditary-kidney-disease,\r\npkd-diagnosis-methods,\r\nkidney-transplant-for-pkd,\r\nkidney-cysts,\r\nnephrology-expert-in-delhi,\r\nchronic-kidney-cyst-disorder]', '2025-01-15', '', 'polycystic-kidney-disease');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `name`, `short_desc`, `image`, `description`, `meta_title`, `meta_disc`, `meta_keyword`, `date`, `tags`, `url`) VALUES
(19, 'Acute Kidney Injury (AKI): How It Differs from CKD', 'Until something seriously goes wrong, kidney health is frequently disregarded. Acute Kidney Injury (AKI), a more abrupt and concerning condition', 'blog19.jpg', '<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Until something seriously goes wrong, kidney health is frequently disregarded.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\"><a href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/contact\"><strong>Acute Kidney Injury</strong></a></span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp;(AKI), a more abrupt and concerning condition, can be just as dangerous as chronic kidney disease (CKD), if not more so. For prompt diagnosis, efficient treatment, and improved health outcomes, it is essential to comprehend the distinctions between AKI and CKD.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\"><a href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/\"><strong>Dr. Sunil Prakash</strong></a></span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>&nbsp;(Vice Chairman and Head of Department Nephrology and Renal Sciences &amp; Kidney Transplant)</strong> highlights that differentiating between AKI and CKD has direct effects on patient survival and quality of life and is not merely a medical formality. Although the kidneys&apos; capacity to filter waste and preserve fluid balance is impacted by both disorders, there are significant differences in their aetiology, course, and approaches to treatment.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Let&apos;s examine the differences between acute kidney injury and chronic kidney disease and how understanding them can help save lives.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><br></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Understanding the Basics</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">It&apos;s important to comprehend the fundamentals of both conditions before delving into the differences.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">What is Acute Kidney Injury?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\"><a href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/contact\"><strong>Acute Kidney Injury</strong></a></span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp;is a sharp drop in kidney function that usually happens over a few hours or days. A triggering event, such as severe dehydration, sepsis, trauma, or certain medications that affect blood flow to the kidneys, is frequently the cause of it. In AKI,&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;the body accumulates toxins as a result of the kidneys&apos; ineffective removal of waste from the blood.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">If identified and treated quickly, AKI is frequently reversible. But if treatment is not received, it may result in death or irreversible kidney damage.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">What is Chronic Kidney Disease?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Conversely, chronic kidney disease is a progressive loss of kidney function that occurs over months or years. CKD is typically brought on by underlying medical conditions such as diabetes, hypertension, or genetic disorders. End-stage renal disease (ESRD), which necessitates dialysis or kidney transplantation, can eventually result from the damage caused by chronic kidney disease (CKD), which is usually irreversible.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><br></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Differences Between AKI and CKD</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">1. Onset and Duration</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The two conditions differ primarily in their rate of development. While CKD develops gradually over time, AKI happens suddenly&mdash;within a few days.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Hospital emergencies such as surgery, infections, or drug toxicity can cause AKI. On the other hand, CKD is frequently identified through routine blood or urine testing and may not exhibit any symptoms in its early stages.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">2. Causes</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The causes of acute kidney injury are often sudden and external, such as:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;\">\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Blood loss or low blood pressure</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Severe infections (sepsis)</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Use of nephrotoxic drugs like NSAIDs or contrast dyes</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Obstruction of the urinary tract</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In contrast, CKD is primarily due to internal, systemic conditions such as:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;\">\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Long-standing diabetes</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Chronic hypertension</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Polycystic kidney disease</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Glomerulonephritis</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">3. Symptoms</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">AKI symptoms may appear suddenly and include:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;\">\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Decreased urine output</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Swelling in legs and ankles</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Fatigue and confusion</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nausea</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Shortness of breath</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>CKD symptoms develop gradually and might include:</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;\">\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Persistent fatigue</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Loss of appetite</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Muscle cramps</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Itchy skin</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Swelling, especially in the feet and ankles</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Remarkably, similar complications such as fluid overload, electrolyte imbalance, and an elevated risk of heart disease can result from both conditions. The main distinction is the speed at which these symptoms appear.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><br></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Diagnosis: How Are AKI and CKD Identified?</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Abrupt changes in kidney function, especially a sharp increase in serum creatinine or a notable decrease in urine output, are the basis for diagnosing AKI. Diagnostic procedures usually involve imaging studies, blood tests, and urine tests.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">On the other hand, chronic kidney disease (CKD) is identified by persistently abnormal kidney function over a minimum of three months. Two important indicators of the advancement of CKD are persistent proteinuria and estimated glomerular filtration rate (eGFR).</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Another significant difference is that if the underlying cause is treated, AKI can occasionally be totally reversed. However, rather than curing CKD, it is managed by slowing its progression.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><br></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Treatment Options</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">Treating AKI</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Treatment for&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\"><a href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/contact\"><strong>Acute Kidney Injury</strong></a></span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp;focuses on:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;\">\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Identifying and treating the underlying cause (e.g., infection, dehydration)</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Discontinuing nephrotoxic medications</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Managing fluid and electrolyte imbalances</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Dialysis (temporary) in severe cases</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Complete recovery is possible with prompt intervention. On the other hand, severe or protracted AKI may develop into chronic kidney impairment.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">Managing CKD</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">CKD treatment is more complex and long-term. It includes:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;\">\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Strict blood sugar and blood pressure control</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Use of medications like ACE inhibitors or ARBs</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Diet and lifestyle modifications (low sodium, limited protein)</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Regular monitoring through labs and imaging</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Preparing for dialysis or transplant in later stages</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">CKD is treated as an outpatient condition with regular nephrology follow-ups, in contrast to AKI, which may necessitate hospitalization and intensive care.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><br></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Risk Factors to Watch Out For</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">AKI Risk Factors:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;\">\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Older age</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Critical illness or hospitalization</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Major surgery</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Dehydration</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Exposure to certain antibiotics or contrast dyes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>CKD Risk Factors:</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;\">\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Family history of kidney disease</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Long-term diabetes</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">High blood pressure</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Smoking</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Obesity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">AKI is more common in people with CKD, particularly while they are in the hospital. In a person with pre-existing CKD, an acute episode of AKI can hasten kidney damage.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><br></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Can AKI Become CKD?</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Indeed, this is a significant clinical issue. Some patients may not fully recover, particularly those who have experienced severe or recurrent episodes of acute kidney injury. Chronic kidney disease may result from irreversible damage to the kidneys.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">This shift from AKI to CKD emphasizes the significance of prompt action, adequate hydration, medication control, and careful monitoring even after hospitalization.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><br></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Prevention: What Can You Do?</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">While some causes of kidney injury are unpredictable, both AKI and CKD share several modifiable risk factors. Preventive strategies include:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;\">\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Staying well-hydrated, especially during illness or exercise</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Avoiding excessive use of over-the-counter painkillers</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Managing blood sugar and blood pressure levels</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Regular check-ups if you have diabetes, hypertension, or a family history of kidney issues</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Prompt medical attention during infections, hospitalizations, or when taking new medications</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Proactive self-care and prompt medical attention are often key to preventing the onset or progression of kidney disease.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><br></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\'margin-top:8.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:21px;font-family:\"Aptos Display\",sans-serif;color:#0F4761;font-weight:normal;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Overall Summary</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Aptos\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Although both&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\"><a href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/contact\"><strong>Acute Kidney Injury</strong></a></span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp;and chronic kidney disease are severe illnesses that impair renal function, there are important differences in how they develop, what causes them, and how they are treated. AKI is sudden and, with prompt treatment, may be reversible. However, CKD progresses slowly and needs to be managed for the rest of one&apos;s life. As&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\"><a href=\"https://www.drsunilprakashkidneyspecialist.com/\"><strong>Dr. Sunil Prakash</strong></a></span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>&nbsp;(Vice Chairman and Head of Department Nephrology and Renal Sciences &amp; Kidney Transplant)</strong> explains that early detection, individualized treatment, and patient education are the keys to improved outcomes in both conditions. Anyone managing their health or providing care for a loved one at risk needs to understand the distinction between the two; it&apos;s not just important for medical professionals.</span></p>', 'Acute Kidney Injury (AKI) vs. CKD: Know the Key Differences', 'Discover how Acute Kidney Injury differs from Chronic Kidney Disease. Learn about symptoms, causes, treatments, and insights from Dr. Sunil Prakash.', '[acute-kidney-injury,\r\nchronic-kidney-disease,\r\naki-vs-ckd,\r\nsymptoms-of-aki,\r\nnephrology-expert-delhi,\r\nkidney-disease-stages,\r\ncauses-of-aki,\r\nckd-treatment-options,\r\ndr-sunil-prakash-nephrologist,\r\nkidney-injury-and-recovery]', '2025-02-03', '', 'acute-kidney-injury');

